# Dev Server Process Rules

The user runs the dev server and bot manually. Both write logs to `logs/server.log` and
`logs/bot.log` via `tee -a` (built into the npm scripts in `apps/server/package.json` and
`apps/bot/package.json`). The user starts them — the AI never does.

## NEVER do this (AI assistant rules)

- NEVER run `npm run dev`, `npm run start`, or any command that starts a server or bot process
- NEVER run `tsx src/index.ts` or any variant that boots the Fastify or bot process
- NEVER start a second server instance — it will corrupt logs via `tee` stream collision
- NEVER write to `logs/server.log` or `logs/bot.log` directly from an AI-issued shell command
  (no `>`, `>>`, explicit pipes or redirects to these files)
- NEVER run `tail -f` or any streaming/watch command on log files
- NEVER run commands whose stdout or stderr could be redirected into log files

Note: the `tee -a` inside `npm run dev` / `npm run serve-bot` is intentional and run by the
**user**, not the AI. Do not remove or modify those scripts.

## For e2e / manual testing

- Use `curl` against the already-running server (port 3000)
- Check if server is running first: `lsof -i :3000`

## Reading logs

Logs are ndjson (pino). Read with a one-shot command only:
```bash
tail -n 100 logs/server.log | cat
```
- NEVER use `tail -f`, `watch`, or any streaming variant
- NEVER redirect the output of a read command back into the log file
